rojection effects account for half of the mass contained within a 15'\nradius of Planck galaxy clusters. We did not detect a background underdensity\nof CMASS LRGs, which also leaves a spatially varying redshift dependence of the\nPlanck SZ selection function as a possible cause for our findings.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Jan 2015 22:09:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
