{"id":"1501.02980","submitter":"Matt Landreman","authors":"Matt Landreman, Gabriel G. Plunk, William Dorland","title":"Generalized universal instability: Transient linear amplification and\n  subcritical turbulence","comments":null,"journal-ref":"J. Plasma Phys. 81 (2015) 905810501","doi":"10.1017/S0022377815000495","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.plasm-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this work we numerically demonstrate both significant transient (i.e.\nnon-modal) linear amplification and sustained nonlinear turbulence in a kinetic\nplasma system with no unstable eigenmodes. The particular system considered is\nan electrostatic plasma slab with magnetic shear, kinetic electrons and ions,\nweak collisions, and a density gradient, but with no temperature gradient. In\ncontrast to hydrodynamic examples of non-modal growth and subcritical\nturbulence, here there is no sheared flow in the equilibrium. Significant\ntransient linear amplification is found when the magnetic shear and\ncollisionality are weak. It is also demonstrated that nonlinear turbulence can\nbe sustained if initialized at sufficient amplitude. We prove these two\nphenomena are related: when sustained turbulence occurs without unstable\neigenmodes, states that are typical of the turbulence must yield transient\nlinear amplification of the gyrokinetic free energy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jan 2015 12:33:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-22"}
{"id":"1501.02981","submitter":"Silvia Viola Kusminskiy","authors":"Martin Schneider, Daiara Faria, Silvia Viola Kusminskiy, Nancy Sandler","title":"Local sublattice symmetry breaking for graphene with a centro-symmetric\n  deformation","comments":"Minimal changes, version as published","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B 91, 161407 (2015)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.91.161407","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We calculate the local density of states (LDOS) for an infinite graphene\nsheet with a single centro-symmetric out-of-plane deformation, in order to\ninvestigate measurable strain signatures on graphene. We focus on the regime of\nsmall deformations and show that the strain-induced pseudo- magnetic field\ninduces an imbalance of the LDOS between the two triangular graphene\nsublattices in the region of the deformation. Real space imaging reveals a\ncharacteristic six-fold symmetry pattern where the sublattice symmetry is\nbroken within each fold, consistent with experimental and tight-binding\nobservations. The open geometry we study allows us to make use of the usual\ncontinuum model of graphene and to obtain results independent of boundary\nconditions. We provide an analytic perturbative expression for the contrast\nbetween the LDOS of each sub-lattice, showing a scaling law as a function of\nthe amplitude and width of the deformation. We confirm our results by a\nnumerically exact iterative scattering matrix method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jan 2015 12:48:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Apr 2015 14:39:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-22"}
